node.text:
Here’s the recipe for the keto vanilla birthday cake I made with Ube cream cheese frosting! This was a fun experiment. I was genuinely surprised by how moist and fluffy the cake came out! BTW, definitely also had “real” cake...and milkshakes...and bread pudding too cuz...there’s no holding back on your birthday!!!

Cake ingredients: 

3 c almond flour
1 c coconut flour
4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1.5 c vegan butter, softened
1.5 c monkfruit sugar
8 eggs
1 c almond milk
2 tsp vanilla extract

Ube cream cheese frosting ingredients:

1 c monkfruit powdered sugar
16 oz vegan cream cheese, softened
1/2 c softened vegan butter
1/2 tsp of ube extract

Method:

1. Mix all cake ingredients together
2. Bake for 45 min - 1 hr depending on your oven, until firm on top, at 350 F
3. Once firm, remove from oven, let cool, then slice into 2 or 3 layers
4. For frosting, whip all ingredients together, then chill in fridge
5. Once both the cake and frosting are cool, add frosting between each layer of cake, and then on the outside
6. Slice and enjoy!

Makes 16 servings!

Recipe adapted from @thebigmansworld keto birthday cake.

1.5 banana + 1/2 c coconut flour

1 banana + 1/2 c rolled oats

1.5 banana + 1/2 c pea protein

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut + 1/2 c peanut powder

Watch the video to find which recipe failed and which recipe won! I’m always looking for an easy staple healthy cookie recipe...which do you wanna try?

node.text:
I love dancing! It is my favorite form of cardio because it never feels like cardio, you know what I mean?! I'm sad that I can't take dance classes or fitness classes right now, but it's all good because we need to do our part to flatten the curve! And that means social distancing!
.
Anyway, my friend @thefitnessmarshall tagged me in the Your Turn Dance Challenge and I was like nooooo SO MUCH CHOREO TO LEARN but once I got started it wasn't that bad. Thank you Caleb for the lil push :) I had a lot of fun getting my groove on, so if you guys wanna learn it too, just follow my tutorial! I tacked on the last 4 counts and YES IT INCLUDES A HAIR WHIP YOU ARE VERY WELCOME.
.
Here's how this all got started BTW!
.
1️⃣Started by @daniellenatoni - this challenge is designed to see how much choreography we can build by each person adding 4 counts at a time!
2️⃣Danielle then threw it to @officialtaniabaron who did her 4 counts who then threw it to @shaunt who threw it to @drlaurenfitz who thew it to @thefitnessmarshall who has now thrown it to me!
3️⃣I added on my own 4 counts inspired by my heels classes and NOW I CHALLENGE MY LIL SISTER @jackelynho to add the next 4 counts!
4️⃣Who will be next and how long will this keep going?!?😍🙌🏼🤷🏼‍♀️
#yourturndancechallenge #dance #dancechallenge #socialdistancing

node.text:
The fitness industry is a weird place. Trainer bodies are treated like billboards and the ones with the best selling programs or the most followers are the ones with the most “desirable” bodies.

It’s the truth. I know this because I’ve lived it.

No matter how much I try to explain that how you look is hugely affected by your genetics, people with great butts can sell booty programs and then I get asked if my workouts even work because of how flat mine is 🙄 Same thing with abs. I have an extremely strong core from years of Pilates but still get asked why I don’t have abs.

On the contrary, whenever I post an arm workout like this one, it always gets a bunch of views because simply put - my arms look lean and cut.

My “billboard” for arms seems trustworthy. Whereas my “billboard” for glutes doesn’t create a strong visual promise for the viewer. It’s a what-you-see-is-what-you-get mentality with fitness, but the truth is, THE BODY DOESN’T WORK LIKE THAT. 

If we’re talking just physical, fat loss and muscle growth happens at different rates in different parts of your body. Plus, it’s all connected! For example…want big boobs and a tiny waist? Many bikini competitors have to get breast implants because they lose so much fat when they get super lean. Even I considered it after I competed for the first time…

Anyway, wanted to share that to tell you this: don’t get sold by a billboard. Go deeper. Look behind the visual and find the joy. The real reason why you’re gonna wake up every morning, even when you’re older, itching to get outta bed and get sweaty. It’s gonna be because you love how it feels. Not because you wanna be skinny. Yeah, maybe that works for a little while, but not forever. Vapid goals die quick.

Oh! And just dropped some new Pilates workouts in @fitonapp! #ad You can’t find these on YouTube or in my app, it’s exclusive, so def go download the app because it’s free. Legit can’t believe it still is with all the cinematic quality workout videos in there! You can even do dance workouts, yoga, HIIT, stretching - it’s a seriously good group of instructors but instead of driving to the gym you can just do everything at home!

♥️Cassey

12 years ago, I visited NYC for the first time in my life. Here’s what was going on:

It was 2009. I had just graduated with a Biology degree that I wanted nothing to do with, my parents absolutely disapproved of me following my passion (design), the recession made it hard to get hired anywhere, and I felt…so lost…so out of place…so defeated. Career wise.

Relationship wise, I had been with my new boyfriend @samlivits for a year at this point and we were madly in love. We didn’t have enough money to get a hotel, so we asked one of Sam’s friends if we could crash with him in his tiny East Village basement. We never took a single yellow cab (walking and subway only!), we mostly ate at food trucks and once in a while treated ourselves to a hole in the wall restaurant, and you know what? It was perfect. We loved the city so much but didn’t know how or when we could visit again.

Well, life has it’s funny ways if you keep pushing, keep believing, and keep being resilient in the face of failure.

Since 2009, Sam and I have flown to New York more than any other city in the world! And the best part? It’s for work…doing things I’m passionate about. The very things my parents told me I need to stop doing because I was “wasting my time”. From teaching Pilates in Times Square to ringing the bell at NASDAQ to appearing on multiple national live TV shows, I seriously cannot believe how far baby Sam and Cassey have come.

And you wanna know something funny? Today after I did my segment on @livekellyandryan teaching Pilates to @mariamenounos and @ryanseacrest using @popflex_active yoga mats and POPFLEX booty bands (omg!!!) we decided to celebrate by walking all the way from Times Square to Washington Park (12,000 steps for fun) and grabbing lunch at some hole in the wall. Then when it started raining a bit, I told Sam I wanted to take a cab back Uptown but he was adamant about taking the Subway. He thinks it’s “fun.” 🤔

Hey. Some things change and some things don’t.

I’m just so happy that today, in 2021, the confidence I have in myself, my business, and my relationship is stronger than ever. I am so grateful for this journey.

♥️Cassey

You know what’s so funny!??? I literally did not intend for this top to be reversible. Nope. It always was a high neck mesh crop top. IT WORKS.

I am always learning something new from you guys 😅 

Anyway! Just dropped this new Marine Marble set on @popflex_active! The Lavender version sold out so quick last time that I wanted to bring this set back in an additional option for you! New color, same ButterSoft.

And seriously…thank you for your enthusiasm. Your love for POPFLEX gives me more confidence as a designer. I never went to school for fashion and sometimes get major imposter syndrome. Every time I see you wear the clothes and how it hugs your body just right, my heart fills with a bit more fullness. I’ll never stop learning in this school of life and I hope to keep making you cool things til I can’t draw anymore.

Honestly. Tastes way better than gluten free bread. 

I just tried airfrying my tofu to turn it into sandwich “bread” slices AND IT WORKS!!! Here’s how:

“Bread” slice ingredients:

▪️1 - 16 oz block of @housefoodsamerica #ad firm tofu, sliced and pressed into 4 “bread” pieces
▪️Mushroom powder or salt & pepper for seasoning

“Bread” method:

1️⃣ Cut block of tofu into 4 slices
2️⃣ Press with paper towels held down by a heavy object to remove excess liquid (10 min)
3️⃣ Coat each slide evenly with mushroom powder or salt & pepper or any seasoning of choice
4️⃣ Place tofu slices in air fryer for 30 min or until both sides are crispy golden. You can also pan fry for a few minutes each side.
5️⃣Then just fill with whatever ingredients you want! 

I used 2 oz of deli turkey along with tomatoes, pickles, ¼ avocado , lettuce, and mustard. It was SO YUMMY, super high protein, and @samlivits approved!

1 sandwich: 348 cals, 14g carbs, 19 fat, 35g protein

I did it. I got bangs.

!!!

(Felt like I needed a change and this was perfect! Still working on length so I won’t be dying it lighter anytime soon.)

So today’s self timer tripod photoshoot theme: Bangs & Bottles!

Happy to announce that the giant @popflex_active bottles are back! Here’s my 64 Oz! As you can see, it’s bigger than my head 😜 I drink 2 a day to reach a full gallon. I fill it with ice and 🍋 slices and it stays cold all day. I take it EVERYWHERE with me like it’s a fashion accessory. I mean truly though - this bottle makes a statement about how serious you are about your hydration. 💧 

It’s generally recommended for you to drink about half your weight (lbs) in fluid ounces. But if that’s too much calculation, try drinking til your pee is lime juice colored. Everyone’s hydration needs are different based on activity level and also climate etc.

My skin is looking clearer these days thanks to the hydration but also maybe thanks to a new skincare routine I’m exploring. I’m not wearing ANY foundation or concealer in these pics and there’s no filter. I’m only wearing tubing mascara (the best for lengthening) and brow powder.

What do you think? Do you like my bangs or are you still trying to get used to them like @samlivits 😅?

♥️Cassey

PS: Thanks @ginaatkinson for the bangs. LOVE.

node.text:
Isn’t it interesting how everyone’s body responds differently to the same exercises?

Like, my arms are fastest to show definition while no matter how much I cut my macros or increase the intensity of my exercise routines (even during bikini competition time) my lower belly always likes to be soft and squishy! 🙃

Exercise programs and meal plans are excellent GUIDES. But when you want very specific results, you  need to do your homework too - explore and write down your body’s specific responses to the different things you’re experimenting with. Comparing with others and getting upset will do no good as your responses are INDIVIDUAL. Oh and let’s not forget that our bodies change with age too, so what used to work might not anymore! We are constantly evolving as humans - mentally, physically, and emotionally.

Anyway, wanted you show you one of my favorite exercises with booty bands! I LOVE working my shoulders and these Banded Upright Rows are just as good as the weighted version. Have you ever tried?!

You can get my knitted bands from @popflex_active - these are the Tropicana designs and they come in light, medium, and heavy in 1 cute travel pouch! 🌴Popflexactive.com

♥️Cassey

node.text:
I used to get upset thinking why women had to be the ones to endure all the pain of pregnancy, childbirth, and post pregnancy while men had it easy.

Whenever @samlivits asked if it was time for us to have a baby, I kept joking, “yeah, anytime if humans could be like seahorses!”

Fun fact: With seahorses, the sperm-producers are also the ones that get pregnant!!! The female transfers her eggs to the male’s abdominal pouch and the male releases sperm to fertilize the eggs as they enter. Then daddy seahorse incubates them for 24 days until the babies are born!

Cool right!?

Anyway, this past weekend I was talking to young moms in different stages of pregnancy or post pregnancy and I heard something that kinda flipped my thinking a bit. One mom said she actually ENJOYED giving birth (I know…what!?!?) because it made her feel powerful, accomplished, and that she was strong enough to endure and conquer this really hard and scary thing. And she told me she wanted to do it again just to feel that feeling once more.

That statement blew me away and I kinda haven’t been able to stop thinking about it. I mean, I live my life in challenges at a time, and the way she put it, kinda spoke to me??? I mean, the whole thing still terrifies me though and I hate pain. I die at period cramps. Yeah, I’m the weakest when it comes to pain tolerance when it’s not of the workout kind 😅

Anyway, to all the women who have done it, you are the true ✨Wonder Women✨!

Thanks to my amazing friend @wendyslookbook for the Wonder Woman outfit transition idea! I’m wearing @popflex_active Tropicana and then changed into a cute beach set I found on ASOS. It was so scary throwing the outfit because it was super windy on Bora Bora and I thought my outfit would land in the ocean. Thank goodness it did not!

♥️Cassey

node.text:
It’s interesting how people ask when you’re gonna have kids as if it’s actually in your control.

I have multiple friends who have dealt with devastating infertility issues and miscarriages, and honestly I did not know how common these things were until social media gave women an easier place to openly share their stories. My mom had a miscarriage, lots of trouble getting pregnant and had to use Chinese herbs to help her conceive.

So even though right now I’m struggling with the whole “do I want to be a mother” thing - who’s to say that if and when both @samlivits and I decide yes, that I actually can???

I’m in my 30s, I have no idea about the quality or quantity of my eggs, my mom had infertility issues, and to be completely honest with you, my menstrual cycles are also longer than the average woman and they are irregular (they have been since high school when I was training intensely for tennis).

I’m thinking of visiting a clinic to get a check up on my fertility status. The more information the better. I’m very curious. But also…if I’m gonna do it, I say, Sam has to do it too!

What’s been your experience with trying? (I have so much to learn!!!)

♥️Cassey

UGH. I love cheesecake so much and I wish I could eat it everyday (but lactose intolerance 😅).

Anyway, my love for desserts primes me for adventurous recipe testing and that’s why I am so excited to be partnering with @housefoodsamerica to come up with fun and creative recipes using TOFU - the perfect blank slate that can be incorporated into most recipes to give a protein boost! #ad

This time I challenged myself to make a healthy dessert smoothie. The best part? Because it’s made with @housefoodsamerica Tofu, it's packed with protein and would make for a great post-workout smoothie to help rebuild and re-fuel my muscles! 💪

It is SOOOOOO GOOOOOD!!!! I made @samlivits try it and he loved it too!

🍓Strawberry Cheesecake Smoothie:

½ 16 oz block of soft tofu from @housefoodsamerica 
½ c frozen strawberries
½ c frozen bananas
¼ c coconut milk 

Macros: 239 cals, 28g carbs, 8g fat, 13g protein

📺 LIVE WORKOUT + COOKING DEMO:

I’m so excited about this recipe that I want to make this for you LIVE! I’m thinking we start out with a 20 min crazy ab workout at 9AM PST on Tuesday July 20, and then afterwards we can chill and make this post workout smoothie together.

OMG so excited. Are you coming?! 🤓

Go get your ingredients now so we can make it live together on Tuesday!

♥️Cassey
